author: wn.com
title: Route 58 finally free of 100 mud-bound vehicles, but mud remains
text: Rescuers threw ladders and tarps across mud up to 6 feet deep to help hundreds of trapped people from cars that got caught in a roiling river of mud along the major Southern California trucking route. Amazingly, officials said, no deaths or injuries were reported. (KABC-TV via AP)
